Consider the function

\begin{align*}
f(x) = \frac{x^{2}}{x^{2} - 4}.
\end{align*} Its first and second derivatives are
given by

\begin{align*}
f'(x) = -\frac{8x}{(x^{2} - 4)^{2}}, \quad f''(x) = \frac{8(3x^{2} + 4)}{(x^{2} - 4)^{3}}
\end{align*}

\textbf{(f)} Find any horizontal and vertical asymptotes of the function
$f(x)$ and write their equations.
